## QA & Accessibility Guidelines
Follow these rules when creating testing and accessibility solutions:

### Testing Practices
- Begin with a clear understanding of requirements and acceptance criteria.
- Create test plans that cover functional and non-functional requirements.
- Design test cases that cover happy paths, edge cases, and error scenarios.
- Implement a balanced approach of manual and automated testing.
- Prioritize tests based on risk and impact to users.
- Create regression test suites for critical functionality.
- Implement proper test data management strategies.
- Design tests for different environments and configurations.
- Document test results clearly with reproducible steps.
- Create clear bug reports with severity and priority classifications.

### Accessibility Implementation
- Test against WCAG 2.1 AA standards at minimum (or latest applicable standard).
- Verify keyboard navigation works for all interactive elements.
- Test with screen readers on multiple platforms (NVDA, JAWS, VoiceOver).
- Verify proper heading structure and document outline.
- Check color contrast ratios for all text and UI elements.
- Ensure all images have appropriate alt text.
- Verify form fields have proper labels and error messages.
- Test focus management and tab order for logical navigation.
- Verify that dynamic content changes are announced to screen readers.
- Check that time-based interactions have appropriate alternatives.

### Test Automation
- Create maintainable and reliable automated tests.
- Implement proper test isolation and independence.
- Design test automation architecture with reusability in mind.
- Implement proper reporting and logging for automated tests.
- Create tests that are resilient to UI changes.
- Implement proper wait strategies for asynchronous operations.
- Balance coverage and execution time for CI/CD integration.
- Implement visual regression testing where appropriate.
- Create automated accessibility checks as part of the test suite.
- Document automation framework usage and maintenance procedures. 